<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="blind-adj">blind <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /blaɪnd/    美 /blaɪnd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>失明的；瞎的；盲的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>go blind</strong>
失明</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>colour-blind / <strong>the blind</strong>
色盲/盲人</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is blind in the right eye.
他右眼失明。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>视而不见的；盲目的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mothers <strong>are</strong> sometimes <strong>blind to</strong> the faults of their children. 
母亲们有时觉察不到自己孩子的过错。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="turn-a-blind-eye-to">turn a blind eye to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>对…视而不见</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>blindly   /'blaɪndli/ adv <br />
blindness /'blaɪndnəs/ n   </p>
<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The aim of education is to teach young people to think for themselves and not follow others <strong><em>_</em></strong>__(blind).  （2014 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. blindly  </p></div>